children.text: There has not been adequate ventilation provided in this sub-floor, resulting in a damp environment, which according to the BCA, encourages timber rot, fungus growth and the potential for termite activity.
Part 3.4.1.2 of the National Construction Code’s Building Code of Australia (BCA) states that
‘Subfloor spaces must be provided with openings in external walls and internal subfloor walls in accordance with Table 3.4.1.1’, see below;
As the BCA classifies this dwelling as being in climatic zone C, the builder will need to increase the ventilation in accordance with part 3.4.1.2 of the BCA.
